WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.480 --> 00:00:02.400
Hey, good morning family.

00:00:02.400 --> 00:00:03.634
Praise the Lord.

00:00:03.634 --> 00:00:05.279
Thank you for joining us today.

00:00:05.279 --> 00:00:09.863
Well, it's Diana and Brandon again, and we have some things on our heart to talk to you about.

00:00:10.274 --> 00:00:20.915
I've been trying to make these videos every day, praying with you and seeking the face of the Lord so that we could be this prayer army that God's called us all to be.

00:00:20.915 --> 00:00:29.599
But there's a lot of people that don't know who we are, where we've come from, and our past, including some of the struggles and successes we've been through.

00:00:29.599 --> 00:00:37.792
Diana and I have been married for quite a while now, going on twenty-some years.

00:00:38.464 --> 00:00:53.051
We set out to be in ministry; it seems like my whole life since I was my son's age, I've always wanted to seek the ministry and have some part of it, even if it was behind the scenes.

00:00:54.194 --> 00:01:05.040
I started traveling and going to Benny Hinn crusades because I saw what he did on TV, and I was like, 'Man, there is something about this.

00:01:05.040 --> 00:01:06.240
Is this fake?

00:01:06.240 --> 00:01:07.262
Is this real?

00:01:07.262 --> 00:01:10.728
' I was just curious as a young kid.

00:01:10.728 --> 00:01:18.933
So, I saved up my money as I worked, put it aside, and would go to crusades.

00:01:19.555 --> 00:01:24.293
My dad, or friends and I, would get in the car and drive long distances.

00:01:26.552 --> 00:01:30.987
I flew to Fort Lauderdale and went to Arkansas and Fort Worth.

00:01:30.987 --> 00:01:36.390
There were a lot of places we went to just to experience the glory because we were hungry.

00:01:43.584 --> 00:01:43.808
I experienced the glory of the Lord there.

00:01:50.524 --> 00:01:54.640
I know he gets a lot of hate now—a lot of people do not like him—and I'm not here to defend him, as I don't know him personally.

00:01:55.600 --> 00:01:58.909
I just know that I experienced the glory when I was there.

00:01:58.909 --> 00:02:07.280
So, if I bring up a person's name, don't throw eggs at me and say, 'Well, you're saying his name; he's of the devil,' and all that.

00:02:07.902 --> 00:02:11.965
I don't believe they're of the devil, or I wouldn't have gone.

00:02:12.826 --> 00:02:24.130
I only went because I knew in my heart I had a pulling to go and experience the glory, the same way I want to experience it with Billy Burke.

00:02:25.599 --> 00:02:27.093
I don't chase people; I chase the glory and the anointing.

00:02:42.153 --> 00:02:42.531
When we got married, I told her, 'Let's go to some crusades.

00:02:42.531 --> 00:02:47.599
' We traveled around and experienced them on our vacations from our ministry jobs.

00:02:47.919 --> 00:02:53.360
I just wanted to be where Jesus was.

00:02:55.312 --> 00:03:01.819
In the back, I was helping because I was a stocky guy—pretty tall and hefty—so I could catch people.

00:03:12.600 --> 00:03:12.730
A guy named Sam saw me and I told him, 'I'm here to volunteer; I want to usher.

00:03:12.730 --> 00:03:17.040
' He said, 'Well, you can help the people down off the stage.

00:03:17.040 --> 00:03:24.352
' I wanted to get as close to the platform as I could so I could see.

00:03:24.352 --> 00:03:30.880
There were times when they wanted me to catch because there were so many people.

00:03:30.880 --> 00:03:38.000
When Benny Hinn took his hand like this, the glory of the Lord knocked me back.

00:03:40.027 --> 00:03:42.660
I couldn't get up off the ground, and I was hooked.

00:03:45.256 --> 00:03:48.107
I called Diana on the phone and said, 'Hey, you'll never believe what just happened.

00:03:57.634 --> 00:03:57.920
I just got knocked off my feet.

00:03:57.920 --> 00:03:59.840
It was amazing.

00:03:59.840 --> 00:04:05.546
' After the service, I went to the back where a man was eating strawberry cake and strawberries.

00:04:05.546 --> 00:04:06.879
I'll never forget it.

00:04:10.106 --> 00:04:10.390
He said, 'Young man, you're the reason I showed up today.

00:04:10.390 --> 00:04:14.933
' I looked at him like, 'Who is this old guy?

00:04:14.933 --> 00:04:18.760
' He said, 'The Lord told me I was supposed to meet you.

00:04:18.760 --> 00:04:21.093
I have a word for you.

00:04:21.093 --> 00:04:30.349
' He said, 'I'm going to meet twelve of you in the next couple of months.

00:04:30.349 --> 00:04:34.686
You're end-time people that will bring healing to the nations.

00:04:34.686 --> 00:04:43.000
' He told me I had a mantle on my life like Kathryn Kuhlman, Oral Roberts, and Benny Hinn.

00:04:49.800 --> 00:04:50.080
He said, 'I'm supposed to pray for you.

00:05:01.090 --> 00:05:01.340
My name is Ralph Wilkerson, and I have Melodyland Christian Center.

00:05:01.340 --> 00:05:06.987
' I didn't know who that was at the time, but I later learned he had a mega-church in Anaheim.

00:05:22.847 --> 00:05:23.055
He said, 'I'm supposed to lay hands on you and impart a double portion of the anointing on my life onto you by what the Spirit of the Lord has told me to do.

00:05:23.055 --> 00:05:28.240
' He laid his hands on mine, and suddenly, the fire of the Holy Spirit went through him into me.

00:05:30.719 --> 00:05:32.853
The palms of my hands felt like I had two hot coals in them.

00:05:32.853 --> 00:05:35.333
He prayed and prophesied over my future, imparting the glory into me.

00:05:35.538 --> 00:05:40.159
I was shook; the power of God was all over me.

00:05:41.360 --> 00:05:46.091
I was forever changed and have never been the same since that impartation.

00:05:52.457 --> 00:05:59.040
At the time, I was working at a grocery store, sacked groceries for years because I had a lot of learning problems.

00:05:59.920 --> 00:06:11.019
I did that until a lady named Debbie called and said, 'Brandon, we have a job for you at the ministry if you want to be a janitor here.

00:06:11.019 --> 00:06:14.130
' I told her, 'I'm not interested.

00:06:14.130 --> 00:06:16.320
I'm called to preach and prophesy.

00:06:18.696 --> 00:06:18.948
I am not a janitor.

00:06:18.948 --> 00:06:23.940
' She said, 'Well, I think you're making a mistake, but if that's your choice, okay.

00:06:23.940 --> 00:06:32.213
' After I hung up, the Holy Spirit said, 'You take that job and you take it now,' rebuking me for my attitude.

00:06:39.510 --> 00:06:44.870
I called her back and said, 'Debbie, I feel the Lord has told me to take this job.

00:06:46.319 --> 00:06:48.240
My flesh doesn't want to, but I'll do it.

00:06:48.240 --> 00:06:53.657
' It was during a 30-day revival called '30 Days of Glory.

00:06:53.657 --> 00:07:00.360
' I started cleaning and helping out, and after the meeting, they hired me full-time.

00:07:10.249 --> 00:07:10.800
Not knowing what God was doing, I started cleaning in the back.

00:07:18.400 --> 00:07:24.530
They had prayer school every Thursday where they taught people to pray, just like I do with you now.

00:07:32.920 --> 00:07:33.210
On my breaks, I would sit in the back and listen to a lady named Gina and Pastor Terri.

00:07:40.670 --> 00:07:45.560
They would pray every Thursday, along with a lady named Annie.

00:07:47.340 --> 00:07:50.779
I listened to them all the time while I was cleaning.

00:07:53.509 --> 00:07:56.939
On Mondays they had healing school, and on Thursdays they had prayer.

00:07:57.249 --> 00:08:00.200
I would listen as they ministered to the sick.

00:08:02.662 --> 00:08:04.790
This went on for three years.

00:08:05.140 --> 00:08:09.463
I started taking care of the ministry plans, the ministry, and the balconies.

00:08:09.463 --> 00:08:13.160
I started going down to the main house of this preacher.

00:08:13.160 --> 00:08:14.660
I took care of things.

00:08:14.660 --> 00:08:19.290
I took care of their cars, I cleaned things, I did a lot; I cleaned carpets.

00:08:19.290 --> 00:08:29.720
So I started getting to go and help out and get things ready for main guest speakers that were coming, like Oral Roberts and a lot of others.

00:08:29.720 --> 00:08:31.894
That's what I did.

00:08:31.894 --> 00:08:40.852
As I kept growing there, I started to have more favor, and I would just keep going because the Lord just had His hand on me.

00:08:42.097 --> 00:08:43.829
Well, I learned to pray.

00:08:44.200 --> 00:08:50.500
They had a guest speaker come to an all-staff meeting; his name was Reinhard Bonnke.

00:08:50.500 --> 00:09:06.959
I don't know if very many of you know who Reinhard Bonnke is, but Reinhard Bonnke was there, and he was telling the people thank you because this main ministry supported a lot of his crusades throughout Africa, and he wanted to say thank you for giving him money to help bring in the lost for Jesus.

00:09:07.253 --> 00:09:12.240
He was praying there, and all of a sudden, he said, 'I feel led to pray for the staff.

00:09:12.240 --> 00:09:14.018
I feel led to pray for the staff.

00:09:14.018 --> 00:09:18.178
So staff, if you feel you want to get prayed for, come down to the front, and I'll lay hands on you.

00:09:18.178 --> 00:09:21.333
' And I think probably everybody went down there.

00:09:21.587 --> 00:09:25.493
I ran down there because I was like, 'This guy's talking about raising the dead.

00:09:25.493 --> 00:09:27.400
He's talking about seeing people get healed.

00:09:27.400 --> 00:09:29.840
He's talking about millions of people getting saved.

00:09:29.840 --> 00:09:32.272
' And I was like, 'I want a part of this.

00:09:32.272 --> 00:09:40.931
' So when he came down to the front, he put his hands on top of my head, and he stopped and said, 'I put a double portion of the anointing on my life onto you.

00:09:40.931 --> 00:09:54.075
' I kid you not, it felt like a bolt of lightning hit me that day and knocked me on my backside again, and in that, I had impartation.

00:09:54.075 --> 00:10:04.288
I got up, and I was forever—I'm telling you, that was one, besides Ralph Wilkerson, that was a forever-changing experience when Reinhard touched me.

00:10:08.880 --> 00:10:23.760
I'm telling you all, I still have that fire of the Holy Ghost stirring on the inside of me, and it's something I—you know, as a kid, you wanted to be bad or whatever, you wanted to go out and hang with your friends.

00:10:25.040 --> 00:10:28.503
But I always had the Holy Ghost always stirring me.

00:10:28.503 --> 00:10:35.888
I couldn't sin without having that in the back of my mind: 'I've got a call in my life.

00:10:35.888 --> 00:10:36.720
I have impartation.

00:10:36.720 --> 00:10:44.280
' It was always something convicting me; I don't know how else to describe it.

00:10:44.280 --> 00:10:50.959
It was just heavy on me, the Holy Spirit telling me, 'Don't do this.

00:10:50.959 --> 00:10:51.840
You've got a call.

00:10:51.840 --> 00:10:52.971
You've got to do this.

00:10:52.971 --> 00:10:57.600
' And then I started having dreams and visions when I started praying.

00:10:57.600 --> 00:11:02.036
I was in the back one day at that church and the Lord spoke to me.

00:11:02.036 --> 00:11:06.870
He said, 'I'm putting a mantle of prayer from this sister that went home.

00:11:06.870 --> 00:11:09.990
' And if I said her name, everybody would know who she was.

00:11:09.990 --> 00:11:13.255
But the Lord said, 'I'm going to give you that mantle.

00:11:13.255 --> 00:11:21.475
And as this comes on you, you will pray and it will be different, and you're going to start to see.

00:11:21.475 --> 00:11:32.800
' So I started looking up on the internet who this woman was and I started trying to find books and teachings about who she was that the Lord told me about.

00:11:36.159 --> 00:11:36.426
And I was like, 'Okay, Lord.

00:11:36.426 --> 00:11:38.400
' So I started studying her.

00:11:39.360 --> 00:11:45.680
And the more I prayed in the back with Gina and them, it just kept bubbling up on me.

00:11:56.057 --> 00:11:58.799
And I started seeing things.

00:12:01.252 --> 00:12:03.339
I started seeing terrorist attacks; I started seeing all kinds of things.

00:12:03.339 --> 00:12:08.639
I'm talking about when 9/11 happened as a young man.

00:12:09.539 --> 00:12:14.090
I saw all that; I had it all down to everything that was going on.

00:12:21.513 --> 00:12:23.632
The Lord showed me and I had specific details of things, and people were like, 'Well, who is this kid?

00:12:23.632 --> 00:12:26.000
' because I was just a young kid.

00:12:26.782 --> 00:12:29.979
I just started seeing the spirit that way.

00:12:34.073 --> 00:12:47.806
And then the more I prayed, the more I sought Him, the more I started seeing angels, the more I started talking, and I had a visitation from Jesus.

00:12:47.806 --> 00:12:55.462
I've had so many visions and impartations of seeing into the spirit realm that I can't count them all anymore; you lose track.

00:13:11.600 --> 00:13:11.863
And I don't say that all to brag; I tell you this because I'm trying to tell you who we are.

00:13:11.863 --> 00:13:13.440
And that's what's happened.

00:13:13.440 --> 00:13:19.786
When the Lord told me to leave Fort Worth and leave that ministry, we came here.

00:13:21.599 --> 00:13:33.839
I thought for sure at that time, because of the way I prayed and things were going on with me, that I was going to step right into ministry at a young age.

00:13:36.240 --> 00:13:37.147
And the Lord called me to be a janitor again.

00:13:52.240 --> 00:13:52.506
I cleaned toilets at that mega-church, learning how a mega-church functions so I could run it with my eyes closed.

00:13:52.506 --> 00:13:54.600
I'm just being real.

00:13:54.990 --> 00:14:06.743
I watched everything and I learned everything I could from the staff to the music, to all of it, how it flowed.

00:14:11.710 --> 00:14:11.980
I was there every Sunday and every Wednesday.

00:14:11.980 --> 00:14:13.600
That was my job.

00:14:23.330 --> 00:14:23.540
I opened it, I closed it, and I set the alarm.

00:14:25.160 --> 00:14:31.519
I was everything; I walked around and cleaned the bathrooms and got everything done.

00:14:45.828 --> 00:14:46.113
And that was what I did for 13 years—10 years on staff like that and then the other time I was doing the floors in other campuses.

00:14:46.113 --> 00:14:53.375
So altogether 13-some years, and it was the longest 13 years of my life.

00:15:08.445 --> 00:15:08.810
So Diana's going to tell her side, what she's done, and I'll let her talk a little bit.

00:15:08.810 --> 00:15:09.542
Yeah.

00:15:09.542 --> 00:15:11.970
So I worked at the ministry too.

00:15:11.970 --> 00:15:17.120
I did the prisoner letters and counted the offerings and that kind of thing.

00:15:17.800 --> 00:15:21.600
And then we met at a Bible study—at Jeremy's Bible study.

00:15:27.120 --> 00:15:27.520
Yeah.

00:15:31.120 --> 00:15:34.464
And then when we moved here, I worked at the grandson of the main minister's.

00:15:34.464 --> 00:15:40.280
We met at a Bible study and we've talked ever since.

00:15:40.280 --> 00:15:49.080
And then when we moved here, when we worked at the other ministry, I counted offerings there as well.

00:15:49.820 --> 00:15:53.600
And after Megan got diagnosed with autism, she was still in diapers.

00:15:53.600 --> 00:15:55.480
It was really, really severe.

00:15:55.480 --> 00:16:02.889
Brendan's told the story; it was a really, really dark time in our life.

00:16:02.889 --> 00:16:07.245
We're still going through that, but we're seeing progress.

00:16:08.959 --> 00:16:12.809
And so that's good, ever since she got prayed over by Billy Burke.

00:16:12.809 --> 00:16:37.390
So, but whenever she was diagnosed at the ministry that we were at, they were telling me that I couldn't work from home and that if I went and got my degree, I might get a promotion, but we would have to pay for it ourselves.

00:16:37.390 --> 00:16:45.227
So I was really praying about it because I really needed to be home with Megan a lot and it was just a lot.

00:16:45.227 --> 00:16:53.227
They said you could be at home working part-time and be there for a season because of how bad Megan was, right?

00:16:53.227 --> 00:16:59.110
But they said one day you're going to have to come back up here.

00:16:59.110 --> 00:17:04.910
They told me I was going to have to go back up there.

00:17:08.827 --> 00:17:15.180
So we were really praying about it and felt that the Lord was leading me to go to ORU.

00:17:15.180 --> 00:17:21.889
They had this program where you could go online, and it was something that I was interested in.

00:17:24.435 --> 00:17:50.148
So I started doing that, and I would work all day at the ministry and then come home and write papers and essays and all the stuff at ORU, do all my tests, watch everything, and I worked on that until sometimes 2:00 in the morning.

00:17:50.148 --> 00:17:53.714
And so I did that for four years for my bachelor's.

00:17:54.752 --> 00:17:55.424
Yeah, four years there at ORU.

00:18:03.200 --> 00:18:03.440
And don't be modest, she made a 4.

00:18:03.440 --> 00:18:08.307
0 all the way through college with her bachelor's, by the grace of God.

00:18:08.307 --> 00:18:09.533
Yes, a 4.

00:18:09.533 --> 00:18:11.659
0 by the grace of God.

00:18:11.659 --> 00:18:15.200
Summa Cum Laude, graduated top of the class for business and for accounting.

00:18:15.200 --> 00:18:16.940
Yeah, got that.

00:18:16.940 --> 00:18:22.160
Then, because you specialized in business and everything, right?

00:18:37.223 --> 00:18:37.600
And then after those four years, then she said, 'Brandon, I feel like I'm supposed to keep going.

00:18:37.600 --> 00:18:39.307
' I said, 'Are you kidding?

00:18:39.307 --> 00:18:45.176
We just did four years, every night of our life for four years.

00:18:45.176 --> 00:18:51.520
' I haven't really got to talk to you because I was taking care of Megan and Braden.

00:18:58.587 --> 00:18:58.791
I told her, "I'm exhausted with this, but if you feel led to go, honey, I'll support you.

00:18:58.791 --> 00:19:02.900
" She said, "Well, it takes three years for my master's, Brandon.

00:19:02.900 --> 00:19:06.674
" Yeah, to do another three years.

00:19:06.674 --> 00:19:10.840
I thought, "Dear God," because I was thinking it would probably be more beneficial pay-wise.

00:19:19.870 --> 00:19:20.120
So I got my major and then my master's in accounting and taxation.

00:19:20.120 --> 00:19:21.600
She made a 4.

00:19:21.600 --> 00:19:23.467
0 all the way through that.

00:19:23.467 --> 00:19:24.960
You cannot skip that part, baby.

00:19:24.960 --> 00:19:25.671
You worked hard.

00:19:25.671 --> 00:19:33.360
She made straight A's through her master's, got an accounting degree, and was able to specialize in taxation, right?

00:19:33.360 --> 00:19:35.526
Taxes and doing CPA stuff for ministries.

00:19:49.520 --> 00:19:49.840
She wanted to do the ministry finances at the church we were working for.

00:19:49.840 --> 00:19:57.840
That was the goal, to be the head of it because it made good money there.

00:20:06.480 --> 00:20:06.720
I was just trying to provide for Megan's needs, and that gets really expensive when you're a parent.

00:20:06.720 --> 00:20:11.199
All her therapists were saying, "You've got to prepare for her future and she needs a savings account.

00:20:24.834 --> 00:20:29.067
" So I was thinking we have to keep going.

00:20:29.067 --> 00:20:37.848
Maybe that'll help make more money if I get my master's, so that's why I just kept going.

00:20:37.848 --> 00:20:50.711
There were so many nights that I would literally crawl into bed crying, and I would say I didn't even understand what I was doing in some classes.

00:20:50.711 --> 00:20:52.830
It was pretty intense.

00:20:52.830 --> 00:20:56.891
There were classes like that—what I'm talking about.

00:20:56.891 --> 00:21:10.650
She would have a problem in some of those master's classes that would take up two or three pages, and she'd keep flipping it over and say, "I got it right.

00:21:20.320 --> 00:21:20.960
" I remember you crying.

00:21:20.960 --> 00:21:24.120
I prayed for you.

00:21:38.160 --> 00:21:38.420
I cried and cried.

00:21:48.880 --> 00:21:49.211
There were several classes where I don't know how I did it other than the grace of God.

00:21:56.747 --> 00:21:57.440
I remember I would just sit there and cry out to God in the shower and say, "Lord, you told me to do this.

00:21:57.440 --> 00:22:04.606
I need some help here because I don't know what I'm doing in this class.

00:22:15.584 --> 00:22:16.048
" Then I would pray, take a break, go back to the class, and see it in a different light.

00:22:16.048 --> 00:22:18.320
That's how I made it.

00:22:18.320 --> 00:22:23.640
Sometimes in the homework I would fail, but I'd make the A.

00:22:23.640 --> 00:22:29.863
Holy Spirit would help bring things to my remembrance and help my memory during the tests to score higher.

00:22:29.863 --> 00:22:38.040
I don't know how she did it other than the grace of God because she didn't have a tutor.

00:22:38.040 --> 00:22:45.325
She watched YouTube videos of someone teaching because the teachers were not very helpful.

00:22:45.325 --> 00:22:51.420
She watched it online, did the course, and did the assignments, and that's all she had.

00:22:51.420 --> 00:23:01.211
Sometimes I told her, "I don't know how you're going to do this," but I was going to pray in the Holy Ghost.

00:23:01.211 --> 00:23:07.778
What really helped was that in high school, I had some really good teachers who taught me how to write essays.

00:23:07.778 --> 00:23:10.799
I was pretty decent at writing essays going into college.

00:23:10.799 --> 00:23:18.840
We wrote so many essays for professors, and I got really good at it.

00:23:29.919 --> 00:23:31.400
The reason I bring up her testimony is that she did all that with two babies.

00:23:31.400 --> 00:23:37.760
One had special needs so severe that we couldn't sleep, functioning off no sleep and staying up.

00:23:37.760 --> 00:23:40.673
We did all this for seven years, pushing forward.

00:23:40.673 --> 00:23:46.000
Now we have a ton of student loans, but we'll get it taken care of.

00:23:46.000 --> 00:23:50.080
It is a major amount of student loans.

00:23:50.080 --> 00:23:54.209
Then, when our pastor fell morally, she had just graduated.

00:23:54.209 --> 00:23:57.492
We were thinking we'd announce she has her degree.

00:23:57.492 --> 00:23:58.919
I'm so proud of her.

00:24:07.700 --> 00:24:07.965
I said, "Baby, you're like Rocky!

00:24:07.965 --> 00:24:08.760
You did it!

00:24:08.760 --> 00:24:13.387
You knocked down the big Russian guy.

00:24:13.387 --> 00:24:16.338
" I told her, "We can do this now.

00:24:16.338 --> 00:24:17.760
We're going to make decent money.

00:24:17.760 --> 00:24:23.010
" We were living on food stamps and barely making it the whole time.

00:24:23.010 --> 00:24:27.160
I told her, "Thank God we're there.

00:24:27.160 --> 00:24:34.857
Maybe we'll make six figures and be able to pay back these student loans.

00:24:34.857 --> 00:24:37.051
" We were so excited.

00:24:37.051 --> 00:24:42.680
The next two weeks, she went in and they said, "We have an announcement to make.

00:24:52.130 --> 00:24:52.320
" The pastor we were working for, who told her she could run the finances, fell morally.

00:24:52.960 --> 00:24:54.240
I got laid off.

00:24:54.240 --> 00:25:02.991
She kept doing the accounting and the offerings, but I told her we had to get out of there because they weren't going to promote her.

00:25:02.991 --> 00:25:10.891
They said they couldn't anymore because they laid off so many people; their finances tanked.

00:25:10.891 --> 00:25:13.573
That happened the year I graduated.

00:25:13.573 --> 00:25:17.671
God had other plans, which was to do eBay.

00:25:17.671 --> 00:25:22.480
That all came through her too, because of learning the business side of things.

00:25:22.480 --> 00:25:29.620
People ask, "How did you learn to hear God the way you hear Him?

00:25:29.620 --> 00:25:33.240
" Well, I had always seen things since I was a teen.

00:25:44.1000 --> 00:25:45.449
I pray and the Lord shows me things, but I started developing the prophetic ear of really hearing the voice of the Lord.

00:25:45.449 --> 00:25:48.799
Don't crucify me, but this is just real.

00:25:48.799 --> 00:25:52.416
Don't get mad when I tell you how I heard.

00:25:57.120 --> 00:25:57.376
It was always watching sports with the Lord.

00:25:57.376 --> 00:26:06.931
That may sound crazy, but I would sit on the couch and we would talk about the score of the game.

00:26:07.780 --> 00:26:13.886
I would pray in the spirit, and the Lord said, "Brandon, I'm going to teach you to hear because you love sports.

00:26:14.057 --> 00:26:20.182
You love basketball, football, and baseball, and I'm going to talk to you so you can practice my presence through this.

00:26:25.160 --> 00:26:25.547
" He would say, "This is who's going to win and in what quarter.

00:26:25.547 --> 00:26:28.520
" He would tell me each thing step by step.

00:26:28.520 --> 00:26:36.600
He would tell me in advance who was going to win the World Series and the Super Bowl.

00:26:36.600 --> 00:26:41.874
I would write it down and tell Diana privately.

00:26:44.409 --> 00:26:50.491
The Lord said this team would win and who would be in the Super Bowl at the end of the year, including the score.

00:26:50.491 --> 00:26:52.062
Every single time, it was right.

00:27:04.416 --> 00:27:04.824
Then he started talking to me about the weather.

00:27:04.824 --> 00:27:09.280
He would say, "On this day, it's going to rain.

00:27:11.520 --> 00:27:11.820
This day, a cold front's coming through.

00:27:22.550 --> 00:27:22.900
In four weeks, this is what's going to happen.

00:27:23.960 --> 00:27:25.759
" He would tell me how much rain we'd get.

00:27:25.759 --> 00:27:30.657
It was always something, but I think my favorite thing was always the weather.

00:27:30.657 --> 00:27:31.760
I loved it.

00:27:32.674 --> 00:27:34.640
He still talks to me about the weather, but not like that.

00:27:34.640 --> 00:27:39.572
Now we talk about everything because it's like we're on here.

00:27:39.572 --> 00:27:47.608
But I loved the simplicity of the relationship back then, how I practiced His presence and we would talk about sports.

00:27:52.600 --> 00:27:52.800
My main thing was the NBA Thunder.

00:28:04.640 --> 00:28:04.871
I would always tell him, and so much so, March Madness came and I would pick the teams that were going to win for March Madness college basketball.

00:28:04.871 --> 00:28:14.480
But the Lord told me, 'If you ever bet or gamble off of what I'm telling you, I'll never speak to you this way again.

00:28:14.480 --> 00:28:15.730
This is something private between me and you.

00:28:16.664 --> 00:28:21.520
You can learn this because you can learn and practice my presence and hear my voice.

00:28:21.520 --> 00:28:26.640
' Brandon, this was something that you did not talk about at the time.

00:28:26.880 --> 00:28:35.270
I never told anybody; I was always private about it, and it was something that Diana and I knew, and my son.

00:28:35.270 --> 00:28:37.120
It was always fun to us.

00:28:37.120 --> 00:28:45.880
We always knew when the weather was coming because God always talked about it.

00:28:55.280 --> 00:28:55.546
I would hear in April how the weather was going to be all through the summer.

00:28:57.102 --> 00:28:57.715
It was really cool, I'm telling you.

00:28:57.715 --> 00:29:00.020
I would write things down.

00:29:00.020 --> 00:29:08.880
I literally told her, 'By this time, this is how the summer will be,' and I'd tell her the temperatures.

00:29:22.977 --> 00:29:23.342
The Lord would tell me how many hurricanes would be in the summer, how many major hurricanes would hit America, and how many major tornadoes would come.

00:29:23.342 --> 00:29:25.795
He would always tell me far in advance.

00:29:36.944 --> 00:29:38.192
I would know exactly how many hurricanes and the category and where they would hit precisely at the location when they would forecast a week in advance.

00:29:38.192 --> 00:29:52.289
I'd see it develop in the Gulf of Mexico or out in the Caribbean, and He would say, 'This is where that hurricane's going to hit, and it's going to hit this town.

00:29:52.289 --> 00:30:00.540
' He would tell me, and I would tell people—I would try to hint around to them.

00:30:15.040 --> 00:30:15.280
I would say, 'Hey, this is where I believe it's going to hit.

00:30:15.280 --> 00:30:19.249
They're all saying it's going to hit here, but...

00:30:19.249 --> 00:30:21.792
' And then whenever Katrina happened, I knew.

00:30:21.792 --> 00:30:27.610
There are just things that the Lord talks to you about, and I'm just being real.

00:30:27.610 --> 00:30:29.360
This is how I learned.

00:30:29.360 --> 00:30:33.013
So Diana and I just kept practicing His presence.

00:30:35.369 --> 00:30:40.640
The more that happened, the more I got confident in hearing Him, and the more He started talking to me and developing other things.

00:30:40.640 --> 00:30:42.680
Then He wanted us to eBay.

00:30:42.680 --> 00:30:52.299
To make a long story short, we started doing that and He started telling me where to go to get stuff out of thrift stores.

00:30:52.299 --> 00:31:02.230
We started doing eBay because we had a bill that was due and we didn't have the money to pay it because he had just gotten laid off.

00:31:02.230 --> 00:31:06.959
We were trying to come up with a way to not have to borrow the money.

00:31:08.863 --> 00:31:15.457
I was praying about it, and I felt in my spirit the Holy Spirit say, 'Just go ahead and start reselling clothes from thrift stores.

00:31:15.457 --> 00:31:17.988
' We only had $100.

00:31:17.988 --> 00:31:36.719
So I told Brandon, 'I think the Lord's telling me that we should take that $100 and I'll go into the thrift store and look for the clothes that He leads me to, that I think I can make a profit on.

00:31:36.719 --> 00:31:42.759
Then we can come up with the money and I'll put everything on auction.

00:31:42.759 --> 00:31:45.496
' That's what we did, and it exploded.

00:31:47.005 --> 00:31:47.211
The Lord blessed our socks off.

00:32:01.387 --> 00:32:01.573
We were able to pay that bill within a day.

00:32:01.573 --> 00:32:05.062
I look at where God has brought us from.

00:32:05.062 --> 00:32:09.227
I'm telling you all, God is no respecter of persons.

00:32:09.227 --> 00:32:25.980
What He did for us in our little journey, whether it's boring to you all or not, I think it's good to talk about it because a lot of people have no clue.

00:32:25.980 --> 00:32:29.479
We're not just people who come on YouTube; we've had a story.

00:32:29.479 --> 00:32:32.540
Everybody has a story and we fought it out.

00:32:32.540 --> 00:32:34.320
We've stuck it out.

00:32:34.320 --> 00:32:36.600
We've been together through very trying times.

00:32:36.600 --> 00:32:44.525
We're still married, we still love each other, and we're passionate about trying to help you all.

00:32:44.525 --> 00:33:02.800
Our heart is to preach to the nations, to lay hands on the sick and do the Great Commission, to do everything that God's called us to do even with all the words that have been given to us.

00:33:02.800 --> 00:33:13.234
When she graduated at ORU—she graduated, not we, though I feel like I'm part of it—the dean of ORU gave her a prophetic word and laid hands on her.

00:33:13.234 --> 00:33:20.423
He said, 'The Lord told me to tell you: you're a prophet to the prophets.

00:33:39.440 --> 00:33:39.640
You and your husband will walk in a very strong prophetic anointing in the days ahead.

00:33:39.640 --> 00:33:46.137
' That was the only word we had ever gotten that told us we are prophetic people.

00:33:54.464 --> 00:33:54.696
He said, 'You'll be a prophet to the prophets.

00:33:54.696 --> 00:34:00.209
' I thought, 'What is that?

00:34:00.209 --> 00:34:04.480
' He laid hands on her and prayed for her.

00:34:13.350 --> 00:34:17.829
I wasn't able to go to the graduation because Megan was so bad; I had to sit out in the car while she went to graduate.

00:34:17.829 --> 00:34:19.707
That was at the honors banquet.

00:34:19.973 --> 00:34:30.030
I went to the honors banquet first and he couldn't even come in because he had to be in the car with the kids because Megan was...

00:34:38.644 --> 00:34:38.995
it was too hard.

00:34:40.399 --> 00:34:42.320
She would have thrown a huge fit.

00:34:43.820 --> 00:34:53.314
I sat out in the parking lot and prayed in the spirit for her while she went in there and had dinner by herself.

00:34:58.109 --> 00:34:58.359
I was really disappointed that night, but it's just part of the pressure.

00:34:58.359 --> 00:35:00.800
Brandon was like, 'You've got to go.

00:35:00.800 --> 00:35:04.103
You earned this.

00:35:04.103 --> 00:35:08.696
' They gave her medals and all this cool stuff.

00:35:13.271 --> 00:35:13.582
I told her, 'You can't miss out on this.

00:35:13.582 --> 00:35:15.449
You worked too hard.

00:35:15.449 --> 00:35:24.593
' So as bad as it was that she had to go by herself, she went.

00:35:24.593 --> 00:35:26.655
She didn't know anybody, but she went.

00:35:26.655 --> 00:35:29.780
We've been through some stuff, y'all, but we're still standing.

00:35:29.780 --> 00:35:38.071
No matter how the waves of life try to knock you down, it's the fight on the inside.

00:35:42.320 --> 00:35:42.560
It's like that little airbag clown that you keep punching and he keeps standing.

00:35:49.337 --> 00:35:49.599
You say, 'Why does he keep getting back up?

00:35:49.599 --> 00:35:52.379
' Because he's standing on the inside.

00:35:55.760 --> 00:35:56.034
That clown is standing on the inside.

00:35:56.034 --> 00:35:58.020
He keeps getting back up.

00:36:08.320 --> 00:36:08.550
You keep punching the airbag because he's standing on the inside.

00:36:08.550 --> 00:36:09.930
There's something about that.

00:36:09.930 --> 00:36:12.502
I believe it's people who stand on the inside.

00:36:12.502 --> 00:36:22.959
No matter how bad life tries to knock you on your hiney and these waves keep coming after you, Diana and I keep fighting through it.

00:36:26.880 --> 00:36:27.080
This is just barely scratching the surface of our testimony.

00:36:34.640 --> 00:36:34.960
There's been a lot of pain in the process.

00:36:34.960 --> 00:36:37.154
People say, 'Well, you need counseling.

00:36:37.154 --> 00:36:38.753
' Jesus has been my counselor.

00:36:45.040 --> 00:36:45.230
I don't need a shrink.

00:36:45.230 --> 00:36:46.370
I've got the Word.

00:36:47.086 --> 00:36:48.137
I may have battle scars.

00:36:49.909 --> 00:36:54.710
You may look at me and go, 'Brandon, you look like you've been through the wringer.

00:36:54.710 --> 00:36:56.338
' Yes, I have.

00:37:01.720 --> 00:37:02.000
I have been through hell, but I've kept walking.

00:37:02.000 --> 00:37:04.160
I refuse to camp there.

00:37:04.160 --> 00:37:07.900
I refuse to be a victim of things that have happened.

00:37:07.900 --> 00:37:20.840
As I told some family members, 'If you lived my life back then for a week, you'd be ready to jump off a cliff.

00:37:20.840 --> 00:37:25.428
' Not many people could have lived it.

00:37:25.428 --> 00:37:29.013
It was by the grace of God.

00:37:30.400 --> 00:37:39.210
And I know there's a lot of you out there that have a worse testimony than us, that have been through trying times.

00:37:39.210 --> 00:37:41.169
We see your letters.

00:37:41.511 --> 00:37:43.120
I cry over them.

00:37:43.840 --> 00:37:51.389
I see some of these letters and what you're going through and I go, "Oh God, I feel it.

00:37:51.389 --> 00:37:52.056
It's real.

00:37:52.514 --> 00:38:15.920
" I just wanted to give you all some hope that if God can do what he has done through dying and walk us through the valley of the shadow of death a lot of times, feeling like his rod and his staff comfort me—that's the kind of God I believe we serve: he is able to bring us out of the pit.

00:38:17.220 --> 00:38:21.439
And it may be that we're still walking out of it.

00:38:21.439 --> 00:38:27.160
We're still coming through the storm, but we're standing up on the inside.

00:38:27.160 --> 00:38:30.469
By the way, my youngest made me this shirt.

00:38:33.314 --> 00:38:35.659
I told her, "Daddy, will you wear that shirt after I made it for you?

00:38:38.329 --> 00:38:46.533
" And I said, "Yes, not only will I wear it, but I'll wear it on my video and everybody on YouTube can see my shirt, baby.

00:38:46.533 --> 00:38:50.587
" So I wore it and she was so excited.

00:38:50.587 --> 00:38:57.920
She grinned from ear to ear when she said, "Daddy, you're really going to wear it on the internet.

00:38:57.920 --> 00:39:04.268
" So, she made it for me.

00:39:04.268 --> 00:39:06.424
She sent me a tie-dye.

00:39:06.424 --> 00:39:07.940
Diana has one to match.

00:39:18.418 --> 00:39:18.676
I should have worn mine.

00:39:18.676 --> 00:39:22.200
She wore hers yesterday, so it's dirty.

00:39:22.200 --> 00:39:24.360
So, we're matching.

00:39:24.360 --> 00:39:26.800
We have matching tie-dyes.

00:39:32.240 --> 00:39:44.248
My little Paisley—the one that raised the dog from the dead, that was out praying over that dog that I stepped on and killed—if you ever hear that testimony, that little firecracker, she's the one that made this.

00:39:44.248 --> 00:39:45.954
She's my little faith buddy.

00:39:45.954 --> 00:39:48.640
She's a praying machine, isn't she?

00:39:48.640 --> 00:39:54.206
She's been baptized in the Holy Ghost since she was three years old.

00:39:54.206 --> 00:39:59.939
Whenever I was praying at night, Braden sits in with me and Diana was sitting there.

00:39:59.939 --> 00:40:07.219
Megan and dying a lot of times would go put Megan to bed because Megan wouldn't go to sleep without Diana laying by her.

00:40:07.219 --> 00:40:22.960
But I put Paisley on my lap or Braden and I sit there and just pray, and the fire of God comes on the kids and then they get baptized in the Holy Ghost and they start praying with me.

00:40:22.960 --> 00:40:24.920
It's the way it's been.

00:40:24.920 --> 00:40:29.013
Braden's been baptized in the Holy Ghost since I think he was two.

00:40:29.013 --> 00:40:31.210
It's just the way it is.

00:40:31.210 --> 00:40:39.872
When you pray and you're a praying family, we just believe in the baptism of the Holy Ghost.

00:40:40.120 --> 00:40:44.100
And we just believe that Jesus Christ is the same yesterday, today, and forever.

00:40:44.100 --> 00:40:50.400
It's real to us, and it's exciting to walk things out by faith.

00:40:50.400 --> 00:40:52.274
So, let's take communion today.

00:40:57.119 --> 00:40:57.359
I hope that video blessed you all.

00:41:09.687 --> 00:41:10.200
It was kind of different, but we thought we'd talk about some of our past.

00:41:15.466 --> 00:41:15.733
And you know what?

00:41:15.733 --> 00:41:22.693
Our past is our past, and we're thankful for what God's brought us: a brand new future tomorrow.

00:41:22.693 --> 00:41:26.120
We're a work in progress, folks, as you can see.

00:41:26.120 --> 00:41:30.960
And so, we're going to take communion right now.

00:41:32.011 --> 00:41:35.646
I don't want to keep drawing this out.

00:41:44.270 --> 00:41:44.440
We didn't want to keep it and make it boring for y'all, but we wanted to tell people where we come from.

00:41:44.440 --> 00:41:47.820
So, let's take communion and see if the Lord shows us anything.

00:41:47.820 --> 00:41:56.514
There's so much going on right now with the earthquakes, with all the stuff happening in the Middle East this week.

00:41:56.514 --> 00:41:57.428
Wow.

00:41:57.428 --> 00:41:59.760
We've had an amazing week, have we not?

00:41:59.760 --> 00:42:02.240
With all this stuff, I go, "Wow.

00:42:02.240 --> 00:42:04.827
" I told Braden, "Every day, this is getting really intense.

00:42:14.640 --> 00:42:14.960
" I told you the labor pains would start to become more and more.

00:42:15.180 --> 00:42:30.160
We would see more and more in the news with the signs of the times—basically what I told you all before even President Trump headed over to the Middle East—that we would see a rising of the finances of the Middle East.

00:42:30.160 --> 00:42:40.840
A great financial wealth transfer will happen with the Middle East, with the prince of Saudi Arabia, Iraq, Syria, and Jordan.

00:42:45.040 --> 00:42:45.656
All these major nations will rise up and become the breadbasket of the world.

00:42:45.656 --> 00:42:50.348
Financial stability like you've never seen before.

00:42:54.640 --> 00:42:55.013
And the Antichrist will rise out of this and show everybody, "I have a solution to all everyone's problems.

00:42:55.940 --> 00:43:00.239
" Even President Trump said, "You know, I really like this guy.

00:43:00.239 --> 00:43:03.180
I don't know why, but I really like this guy.

00:43:03.180 --> 00:43:04.613
" Everybody's going to like him.

00:43:08.920 --> 00:43:09.050
He's just a really nice guy.

00:43:12.480 --> 00:43:12.600
And this is why people say, "Brandon, I don't believe it.

00:43:12.600 --> 00:43:15.456
He seems like he's kind of goofy or whatever.

00:43:15.456 --> 00:43:37.947
" Folks, are you expecting the Antichrist to show up with a sign that says, "I'm an Antichrist," have a big AC tattooed on his head with devil horns and a red cape going, "Haha, I'm the Antichrist"?

00:43:37.947 --> 00:43:42.426
Nobody's going to like you if you come out like that, are they?

00:43:42.426 --> 00:44:07.004
If you expect all the nations of the earth to submit their kingdom to you and you come out saying, "Hey, I'm what the Bible said, I'm the Antichrist," do you think if he comes out and says that, everybody's going to go, "I know the outcome of this"?

00:44:07.004 --> 00:44:08.231
What's going to happen?

00:44:08.231 --> 00:44:12.654
He's going to have to come out deceitful, isn't he?

00:44:12.654 --> 00:44:18.960
I mean, seriously, let the elevator go to the top.

00:44:18.960 --> 00:44:25.359
Do you think he's going to come out with his cabinet and his posse behind him?

00:44:30.994 --> 00:44:31.383
All his influencers, social media—click, click, click.

00:44:31.383 --> 00:44:34.000
Let's put him on social media.

00:44:34.000 --> 00:44:35.920
He's on TikTok.

00:44:54.813 --> 00:44:55.206
"I'm the AC.

00:44:55.206 --> 00:45:07.359
" Like the bozo with the black cape came out and said he's the false prophet and all these things.

00:45:07.359 --> 00:45:10.079
He is a false prophet.

00:45:10.079 --> 00:45:12.811
This guy, he ain't nothing.

00:45:12.811 --> 00:45:29.039
You're going to see a man of great "it factor"—an X-factor that people are going to go, "What is it about him?

00:45:29.039 --> 00:45:37.165
" He's not going to come out with the devil behind him going, "Just let everybody know, follow me.

00:45:37.165 --> 00:45:41.010
" Seriously, we got to be smarter than that.

00:45:42.060 --> 00:45:42.270
"I'm the Antichrist.

00:45:42.270 --> 00:45:46.160
" I really don't understand what people are thinking.

00:45:46.160 --> 00:45:50.480
He's coming out subtle: "I'm a nice guy.

00:45:50.480 --> 00:45:53.257
You want to be my friend?

00:45:53.257 --> 00:45:54.629
Follow me.

00:45:54.629 --> 00:45:57.100
Let's do a financial system together.

00:45:57.100 --> 00:46:05.000
" Then Elon Musk, his buddy with Starlink—"I'm going to give you all Starlink.

00:46:05.000 --> 00:46:08.577
" I said, "My God, there it is, Braden.

00:46:08.577 --> 00:46:08.826
There he is.

00:46:08.826 --> 00:46:10.817
Let's introduce Starlink to Saudi Arabia.

00:46:10.817 --> 00:46:13.146
Let's introduce Starlink to the Middle East.

00:46:13.146 --> 00:46:22.080
" Well, you can buy it from me because he's lost all this money through all these people in DOGE being mad at him.

00:46:22.080 --> 00:46:23.040
"We'll burn your cars.

00:46:23.040 --> 00:46:24.897
We'll do this.

00:46:24.897 --> 00:46:28.580
" So, he's lost all this money.

00:46:28.580 --> 00:46:30.000
So, guess what?

00:46:30.000 --> 00:46:35.989
Trump comes on and says, "I'll let you get some income coming in, buddy, through the Middle East.

00:46:35.989 --> 00:46:58.400
So, you come with me in the airplane and we'll go over there and make some business deals for you and get back all that income you lost through the stock market over the last five months trying to help out the United States.

00:46:58.400 --> 00:47:20.596
Let's get some business deals for you and you'll make all that back, plus a surplus of what you lost, and I'll make you even richer than what you are, because the Prince of Saudi Arabia is going to like you because I like you.

00:47:21.253 --> 00:47:23.303
You and I are homeboys, right?

00:47:32.366 --> 00:47:32.640
" So you got the homeboy with Elon Musk.

00:47:33.520 --> 00:47:35.839
And I told you: watch Neuralink, watch Neuralink, watch Starlink.

00:47:35.839 --> 00:47:36.919
Here he is.

00:47:36.919 --> 00:47:40.231
He's walking over there and everybody likes him.

00:47:40.231 --> 00:47:43.839
